:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-XxNYO eWQzGj pf-848_"><p class="sc-jUosCB eIJFN pf-849_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">1. Decide what kind of shop you want to have</p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-5341" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-hAcGzb jHOovW pf-851_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-eGPXGI cIlovf"><div class="sc-iCfMLu eehqFj pf-852_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-XxNYO eWQzGj pf-853_"><p class="sc-jUosCB eIJFN pf-854_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The first question you need to ask yourself is “What kind of ice cream shop do I want to run and what kinds of products do I want to sell?” Answering this question isn’t all that easy, and you'll need to consider various factors, such as: </p><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-jHkVzv gbyaRg pf-856_"><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bQtKYq wvgEH pf-857_"><b>Customer preferences:</b> Are you going to sell froyo, traditional ice cream, gelato, Italian ices, gelatis, or something else? Conduct surveys and ask people about their preferences to determine which one you should sell. Learn about the differences between ice cream, gelato, and custard.</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bQtKYq wvgEH pf-859_"><b>Competition:</b> Scope out your competition by visiting other ice cream shops in your area. What are they offering and why? What can you learn from them?</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bQtKYq wvgEH pf-861_"><b>Service style:</b> Consider whether you want to offer self-serve options and charge by weight, or have employees serve the ice cream and charge per scoop or cup size.</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bQtKYq wvgEH pf-863_"><b>Location:</b> Do you want an ice cream truck or a brick-and-mortar location? Trucks offer more location flexibility, while a physical store can accommodate more storage and machines.</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bQtKYq wvgEH pf-865_"><b>Franchising:</b> You could also join an ice cream shop franchise to benefit from their established name and systems, but this option can be pricey.</li></ul></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-XxNYO eWQzGj pf-867_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0268/4508/5731/files/Screen_Shot_2024-01-11_at_8.25.32_AM.png?v=1704986795" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0268/4508/5731/files/Screen_Shot_2024-01-11_at_8.25.32_AM.png?v=1704986795 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0268/4508/5731/files/Screen_Shot_2024-01-11_at_8.25.32_AM_500x.png?v=1704986795 320w" width="479" height="421" alt="Gelato in Store" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-868_"/></div></div></div><div class="sc-iCfMLu eehqFj pf-869_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-XxNYO eWQzGj pf-870_"><p class="sc-jUosCB eIJFN pf-871_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 2. Seasonal or year-round operation?</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-iCfMLu eehqFj pf-873_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-XxNYO eWQzGj pf-874_"><div class="sc-iCfMLu eehqFj pf-875_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-XxNYO eWQzGj pf-876_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0268/4508/5731/files/D403DB92-23D3-4245-A6A2-70327DB03997_4_5005_c.jpg?v=1704823653" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0268/4508/5731/files/D403DB92-23D3-4245-A6A2-70327DB03997_4_5005_c.jpg?v=1704823653 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0268/4508/5731/files/D403DB92-23D3-4245-A6A2-70327DB03997_4_5005_c_500x.jpg?v=1704823653 320w" width="476" height="316" alt="Hand Holding Ice Cream" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-877_"/></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-XxNYO eWQzGj pf-878_"><p class="sc-jUosCB eIJFN pf-879_ pf-gs-paragraph-1" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Since most ice cream sales happen in the summer, you'll need to decide whether to operate seasonally or year-round. This decision will depend on factors such as demand, available resources, and your location's climate.&nbsp;<br><br>For example, if you're in a warm state like Florida, you might consider operating year-round. On the other hand, if you're in a colder state like New York, you could pivot to offering winter-friendly products like hot chocolate and baked goods or operate seasonally.<br></p></div></div></div><p class="sc-jUosCB eIJFN pf-881_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">3. Profitability of your ice cream shop</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-iCfMLu eehqFj pf-883_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-XxNYO eWQzGj pf-884_"><div class="sc-iCfMLu eehqFj pf-885_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-XxNYO eWQzGj pf-886_"><p class="sc-jUosCB eIJFN pf-887_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><a href="https://frozendessertsupplies.com/collections/waffle-cone-supplies" target="_blank"></a><a href="http://frozendessertsupplies.com/products/cone-genie-automated-waffle-cone-forming-tool?_pos=6&amp;_sid=bbfd8722c&amp;_ss=r" target="_blank"></a><a href="https://www.amazon.com/Reeses-Peanut-Butter-Sauce-Lbs/dp/B00I3303L2/ref=sr_1_1?crid=GH7XI0K6068U&amp;keywords=peanut+butter+sauce&amp;qid=1679432036&amp;s=grocery&amp;sprefix=peanut+butter+sauce%2Cgrocery%2C165&amp;sr=1-1" target="_blank"></a>According to Ice Cream University, a standard ice cream shop has a profit margin of about 25%. To break even, you'll need to sell at least $4 worth of products for every $1 spent.&nbsp;To boost your profitability, consider offering artisanal ice cream, ice cream cakes, unique shakes, or other frozen treats. The key is to create products with high perceived value, allowing you to charge more and increase your profit margin.<br></p></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-XxNYO eWQzGj pf-889_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0268/4508/5731/files/Starting_an_ice_cream_shop.jpg?v=1643391349" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0268/4508/5731/files/Starting_an_ice_cream_shop.jpg?v=1643391349 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0268/4508/5731/files/Starting_an_ice_cream_shop_500x.jpg?v=1643391349 320w" width="1495" height="1535" alt="Woman Recieving Ice Cream at Shop" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-890_"/></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="sc-iCfMLu eehqFj pf-891_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-XxNYO eWQzGj pf-892_"><p class="sc-jUosCB eIJFN pf-893_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;4. Navigating local licensing laws</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-iCfMLu eehqFj pf-895_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-XxNYO eWQzGj pf-896_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0268/4508/5731/files/Starting_a_ice_cream_truck.jpg?v=1643391241" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0268/4508/5731/files/Starting_a_ice_cream_truck.jpg?v=1643391241 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0268/4508/5731/files/Starting_a_ice_cream_truck_500x.jpg?v=1643391241 320w" width="3260" height="2445" alt="Old Ice Cream Shop" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-897_"/></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-XxNYO eWQzGj pf-898_"><p class="sc-jUosCB eIJFN pf-899_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Local governments have their own rules regarding licenses and permits for ice cream shops, so consult with city officials to ensure you're following all necessary regulations. You may need permits for food processing, business insurance, and a business bank account.<u><a href="http://www.amazon.com/Pascha-Organic-Unsweetened-Chocolate-Baking/dp/B019NQWFAO/ref=sxin_16_pa_sp_search_thematic_sspa?content-id=amzn1.sym.eba7bd4e-dedb-4570-b09b-0e101a3c98a8%3Aamzn1.sym.eba7bd4e-dedb-4570-b09b-0e101a3c98a8&amp;crid=MTAZ0VVTKQPB&amp;cv_ct_cx=bulk+chocolate+chips&amp;keywords=bulk+chocolate+chips&amp;pd_rd_i=B019NQWFAO&amp;pd_rd_r=77e1c7c6-3094-41f2-beb2-ff6b295c373e&amp;pd_rd_w=XofH2&amp;pd_rd_wg=LcIKp&amp;pf_rd_p=eba7bd4e-dedb-4570-b09b-0e101a3c98a8&amp;pf_rd_r=AVQNA4KC9VB73Z1ZMTMG&amp;qid=1679433111&amp;s=grocery&amp;sbo=RZvfv%2F%2FHxDF%2BO5021pAnSA%3D%3D&amp;sprefix=bulk+chocolate+chip%2Cgrocery%2C154&amp;sr=1-1-492482ea-2ad3-4cfe-9d1a-0efc7c5c9374-spons&amp;psc=1&amp;spLa=ZW5jcnlwdGVkUXVhbGlmaWVyPUFGM0hSUDNGOFkwUTkmZW5jcnlwdGVkSWQ9QTA5MDMwODFNUFVUVlBCSkUyTFMmZW5jcnlwdGVkQWRJZD1BMDQ5OTgwNzFaU0ZRU0JFUkZVVk4md2lkZ2V0TmFtZT1zcF9zZWFyY2hfdGhlbWF0aWMmYWN0aW9uPWNsaWNrUmVkaXJlY3QmZG9Ob3RMb2dDbGljaz10cnVl" target="_blank"><span style="color: rgb(37, 191, 204);"></span></a></u></p></div></div></div><div class="sc-iCfMLu eehqFj pf-901_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-XxNYO eWQzGj pf-902_"><p class="sc-jUosCB eIJFN pf-903_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">5. Make or buy your ice cream?</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-iCfMLu eehqFj pf-905_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-XxNYO eWQzGj pf-906_"><p class="sc-jUosCB eIJFN pf-907_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Decide whether you'll make your own ice cream or purchase it from a supplier. Making your own can save on overhead costs and add value to your brand but requires more time and expertise.<u><a href="https://www.amazon.com/Cupcake-Bites-Topping-TableTop-King/dp/B079RJR1LB/ref=sr_1_2?crid=2FU6HECH6FAW8&amp;keywords=cupcake+bites&amp;qid=1679432467&amp;s=grocery&amp;sprefix=cupcake+bites%2Cgrocery%2C168&amp;sr=1-2" target="_blank"><span style="color: rgb(37, 191, 204);"></span></a></u></p></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-XxNYO eWQzGj pf-909_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0268/4508/5731/files/ice-cream-g3dd4e63bf_1280.jpg?v=1648830333" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0268/4508/5731/files/ice-cream-g3dd4e63bf_1280.jpg?v=1648830333 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0268/4508/5